{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896204728,"sessionID":"ses_28456ee41ffeBVl5njyNx1JzXZ","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba978b7001bBcTBRUD8pZFOH","messageID":"msg_d7ba96af1001ej62mXlCS3S5GU","sessionID":"ses_28456ee41ffeBVl5njyNx1JzXZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n2: \n3: > **AR ID:** AR-024  \n4: > **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n5: > **Language:** Python  \n6: > **Size:** M  \n7: > **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Overview\n12: \n13: The `DockerService` class provides a unified, high-level interface for Docker image operations within the AgentCube CLI. This service abstracts Docker SDK interactions for image building, tagging, pushing, and management, providing consistent error handling, logging, and result formatting across the CLI toolchain.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## ST-4.1 — Core Service Implementation Verification\n18: \n19: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n20: |---|------|--------------|------|\n21: | 4.1.1 | Verify `DockerService` class exists in `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | File exists with proper docstring | 0.25h |\n22: | 4.1.2 | Verify `__init__(verbose=False)` initializes logger correctly | Logger level set based on verbose flag | 0.25h |\n23: | 4.1.3 | Verify `_get_client()` lazy-initializes Docker client with `from_env()` | Client created on first access, cached subsequently | 0.5h |\n24: | 4.1.4 | Verify `_get_client()` performs health check via `ping()` | Raises RuntimeError if Docker unavailable | 0.5h |\n25: | 4.1.5 | Verify `is_docker_available()` returns bool without raising | Returns True/False based on Docker daemon status | 0.25h |\n26: | 4.1.6 | Verify `_format_image_id()` helper truncates to 12 chars | \"sha256:abc123...\" → \"abc123\" (12 chars) | 0.25h |\n27: \n28: **Deliverable:** Core service structure verified and working.\n29: \n30: ---\n31: \n32: ## ST-4.2 — Image Building Implementation\n33: \n34: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n35: |---|------|--------------|------|\n36: | 4.2.1 | Verify `build_image()` validates Dockerfile exists | Raises FileNotFoundError with path | 0.25h |\n37: | 4.2.2 | Verify `build_image()` validates context path exists | Raises FileNotFoundError with path | 0.25h |\n38: | 4.2.3 | Verify `build_image()` computes relative Dockerfile path | Path relative to context calculated correctly | 0.5h |\n39: | 4.2.4 | Verify `build_image()` passes build_args to Docker | buildargs parameter populated correctly | 0.5h |\n40: | 4.2.5 | Verify `build_image()` tracks build duration | build_time field in result (seconds) | 0.25h |\n41: | 4.2.6 | Verify `build_image()` formats image size as \"XX.XXMB\" | Size converted from bytes to MB | 0.25h |\n42: | 4.2.7 | Verify `build_image()` extracts error from BuildError logs | RuntimeError includes specific error message | 0.5h |\n43: | 4.2.8 | Verify `build_image()` returns correct result dict | Contains all 6 required fields per spec | 0.5h |\n44: \n45: **Deliverable:** Image building works with proper error handling and result formatting.\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ## ST-4.3 — Image Tagging Implementation\n50: \n51: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n52: |---|------|--------------|------|\n53: | 4.3.1 | Verify `tag_image()` gets source image via client | `client.images.get(full_source)` called | 0.25h |\n54: | 4.3.2 | Verify `tag_image()` applies new tag via `image.tag()` | Tagging method invoked correctly | 0.25h |\n55: | 4.3.3 | Verify `tag_image()` returns result dict with source/target | Dict contains source, target, image_id | 0.25h |\n56: | 4.3.4 | Verify `tag_image()` handles DockerException | RuntimeError raised with context | 0.25h |\n57: \n58: **Deliverable:** Image tagging works end-to-end.\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## ST-4.4 — Image Information & Listing\n63: \n64: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n65: |---|------|--------------|------|\n66: | 4.4.1 | Verify `get_image_info()` retrieves image via `client.images.get()` | Image fetched by full tag | 0.25h |\n67: | 4.4.2 | Verify `get_image_info()` formats size as \"XX.XXMB\" | Size field formatted correctly | 0.25h |\n68: | 4.4.3 | Verify `get_image_info()` returns all required fields | name, tag, id, size, created, labels | 0.25h |\n69: | 4.4.4 | Verify `get_image_info()` raises RuntimeError on missing image | Error message includes full tag | 0.25h |\n70: | 4.4.5 | Verify `list_images()` calls `client.images.list()` | List method invoked with name filter | 0.25h |\n71: | 4.4.6 | Verify `list_images()` handles images without tags | \"<none>:<none>\" default tag handling | 0.5h |\n72: | 4.4.7 | Verify `list_images()` returns list of image dicts | Each dict has name, tag, id, size, created | 0.25h |\n73: | 4.4.8 | Verify `list_images()` supports optional name filter | name parameter passed to client | 0.25h |\n74: \n75: **Deliverable:** Image querying and listing works correctly.\n76: \n77: ---\n78: \n79: ## ST-4.5 — Image Push Implementation\n80: \n81: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n82: |---|------|--------------|------|\n83: | 4.5.1 | Verify `push_image()` constructs full image name with registry | Registry URL prepended when provided | 0.25h |\n84: | 4.5.2 | Verify `push_image()` gets local image before push | `client.images.get(local_tag)` called | 0.25h |\n85: | 4.5.3 | Verify `push_image()` tags image for registry when needed | `image.tag()` called with registry prefix | 0.25h |\n86: | 4.5.4 | Verify `push_image()` logs in when credentials provided | `client.login()` called with username/password | 0.5h |\n87: | 4.5.5 | Verify `push_image()` streams push logs with decode=True | Stream=True and decode=True parameters | 0.25h |\n88: | 4.5.6 | Verify `push_image()` detects errors in push logs | RuntimeError raised on error in stream | 0.5h |\n89: | 4.5.7 | Verify `push_image()` returns result dict with pushed=True | Dict contains image_name, tag, registry, pushed | 0.25h |\n90: | 4.5.8 | Verify `push_image()` handles DockerException | RuntimeError raised with error message | 0.25h |\n91: \n92: **Deliverable:** Image push works with authentication and error detection.\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## ST-4.6 — Credential Extraction\n97: \n98: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n99: |---|------|--------------|------|\n100: | 4.6.1 | Verify `extract_credentials_from_url()` parses user:pass@host format | Credentials extracted from URL | 0.25h |\n101: | 4.6.2 | Verify `extract_credentials_from_url()` URL-decodes credentials | Special characters like @, # decoded | 0.5h |\n102: | 4.6.3 | Verify `extract_credentials_from_url()` reconstructs clean URL | Credentials removed from returned URL | 0.25h |\n103: | 4.6.4 | Verify `extract_credentials_from_url()` handles URLs without credentials | Returns original URL, None for user/pass | 0.25h |\n104: | 4.6.5 | Verify `extract_credentials_from_url()` preserves port if present | Port included in clean URL | 0.25h |\n105: \n106: **Deliverable:** Credential extraction works for embedded auth URLs.\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: ## ST-4.7 — Service Export Verification\n111: \n112: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n113: |---|------|--------------|------|\n114: | 4.7.1 | Verify `DockerService` exported from `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Import works: `from agentcube.services import DockerService` | 0.25h |\n115: | 4.7.2 | Verify `DockerService` in `__all__` list | Listed in __all__ exports | 0.25h |\n116: \n117: **Deliverable:** Service is properly importable from package.\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: ## ST-4.8 — Unit Tests — DockerService Core\n122: \n123: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n124: |---|------|--------------|------|\n125: | 4.8.1 | Write `TestDockerServiceInit` — initialization with verbose=True | Logger set to DEBUG level | 0.5h |\n126: | 4.8.2 | Write `TestDockerServiceInit` — initialization with verbose=False | Logger set to INFO level | 0.5h |\n127: | 4.8.3 | Write `TestDockerServiceClient` — _get_client creates client once | Client cached, from_env called once | 0.5h |\n128: | 4.8.4 | Write `TestDockerServiceClient` — _get_client raises on DockerException | RuntimeError raised with message | 0.5h |\n129: | 4.8.5 | Write `TestDockerServiceClient` — _get_client calls ping() | Health check performed | 0.5h |\n130: | 4.8.6 | Write `TestDockerServiceAvailability` — is_docker_available True | Returns True when ping succeeds | 0.5h |\n131: | 4.8.7 | Write `TestDockerServiceAvailability` — is_docker_available False | Returns False when ping fails | 0.5h |\n132: \n133: **Deliverable:** Core service tests pass with >80% coverage.\n134: \n135: ---\n136: \n137: ## ST-4.9 — Unit Tests — Image Building\n138: \n139: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n140: |---|------|--------------|------|\n141: | 4.9.1 | Write `TestBuildImage` — successful build with minimal args | Result dict contains all fields | 1h |\n142: | 4.9.2 | Write `TestBuildImage` — build with custom build_args | buildargs passed to client.build | 0.5h |\n143: | 4.9.3 | Write `TestBuildImage` — build with proxy build_args | HTTP_PROXY/HTTPS_PROXY handled | 0.5h |\n144: | 4.9.4 | Write `TestBuildImage` — missing Dockerfile raises FileNotFoundError | Exception raised with path | 0.5h |\n145: | 4.9.5 | Write `TestBuildImage` — missing context raises FileNotFoundError | Exception raised with path | 0.5h |\n146: | 4.9.6 | Write `TestBuildImage` — BuildError extracts error message | RuntimeError includes build error | 1h |\n147: | 4.9.7 | Write `TestBuildImage` — image size formatted correctly | Size in MB format (e.g., \"150.50MB\") | 0.5h |\n148: | 4.9.8 | Write `TestBuildImage` — image ID truncated to 12 chars | ID shortened from full sha256 | 0.5h |\n149: | 4.9.9 | Write `TestBuildImage` — build time tracked | Duration in seconds returned | 0.5h |\n150: \n151: **Deliverable:** Build tests pass with >80% coverage.\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ## ST-4.10 — Unit Tests — Image Tagging & Info\n156: \n157: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n158: |---|------|--------------|------|\n159: | 4.10.1 | Write `TestTagImage` — successful tagging | Result contains source, target, image_id | 0.5h |\n160: | 4.10.2 | Write `TestTagImage` — DockerException handling | RuntimeError raised on failure | 0.5h |\n161: | 4.10.3 | Write `TestGetImageInfo` — existing image info retrieved | All fields present in result | 0.5h |\n162: | 4.10.4 | Write `TestGetImageInfo` — missing image raises RuntimeError | Error includes image name | 0.5h |\n163: | 4.10.5 | Write `TestGetImageInfo` — size formatted as MB | Size field formatted correctly | 0.5h |\n164: | 4.10.6 | Write `TestListImages` — list all images | Returns list of image dicts | 0.5h |\n165: | 4.10.7 | Write `TestListImages` — filter by name | name parameter passed to client | 0.5h |\n166: | 4.10.8 | Write `TestListImages` — handles untagged images | \"<none>:<none>\" default tag | 0.5h |\n167: \n168: **Deliverable:** Tagging and info tests pass with >80% coverage.\n169: \n170: ---\n171: \n172: ## ST-4.11 — Unit Tests — Image Push\n173: \n174: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n175: |---|------|--------------|------|\n176: | 4.11.1 | Write `TestPushImage` — push without registry | Local tag used, pushed=True | 0.5h |\n177: | 4.11.2 | Write `TestPushImage` — push with registry URL | Image tagged with registry prefix | 0.5h |\n178: | 4.11.3 | Write `TestPushImage` — push with authentication | client.login() called with credentials | 0.5h |\n179: | 4.11.4 | Write `TestPushImage` — push error detection | RuntimeError raised on error in stream | 1h |\n180: | 4.11.5 | Write `TestPushImage` — push logs processed | Status messages logged at DEBUG | 0.5h |\n181: | 4.11.6 | Write `TestPushImage` — missing image raises error | RuntimeError when image not found | 0.5h |\n182: | 4.11.7 | Write `TestPushImage` — DockerException handling | RuntimeError raised with message | 0.5h |\n183: \n184: **Deliverable:** Push tests pass with >80% coverage.\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## ST-4.12 — Unit Tests — Credential Extraction\n189: \n190: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n191: |---|------|--------------|------|\n192: | 4.12.1 | Write `TestExtractCredentials` — basic user:pass@host | Correct url, user, pass returned | 0.5h |\n193: | 4.12.2 | Write `TestExtractCredentials` — URL encoded special chars | @ and # decoded correctly | 0.5h |\n194: | 4.12.3 | Write `TestExtractCredentials` — no credentials in URL | Original url, None for user/pass | 0.5h |\n195: | 4.12.4 | Write `TestExtractCredentials` — port preserved | Port included in clean URL | 0.5h |\n196: | 4.12.5 | Write `TestExtractCredentials` — query string preserved | Query parameters in clean URL | 0.5h |\n197: \n198: **Deliverable:** Credential extraction tests pass with 100% coverage.\n199: \n200: ---\n201: \n202: ## ST-4.13 — Integration Tests\n203: \n204: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n205: |---|------|--------------|------|\n206: | 4.13.1 | Create `tests/integration/test_docker_service.py` with fixtures | File exists with DockerService fixture | 0.5h |\n207: | 4.13.2 | Test `is_docker_available()` with real Docker | Returns True/False based on daemon | 0.5h |\n208: | 4.13.3 | Test `build_image()` with real Dockerfile | Image built, result contains ID | 1.5h |\n209: | 4.13.4 | Test `get_image_info()` for built image | Info matches built image | 0.5h |\n210: | 4.13.5 | Test `list_images()` includes built image | Image appears in list | 0.5h |\n211: | 4.13.6 | Test `tag_image()` creates new tag | Both tags reference same image | 0.5h |\n212: | 4.13.7 | Test full build → tag → info flow | End-to-end workflow works | 1h |\n213: \n214: **Deliverable:** Integration tests pass with real Docker daemon.\n215: \n216: ---\n217: \n218: ## ST-4.14 — Documentation\n219: \n220: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n221: |---|------|--------------|------|\n222: | 4.14.1 | Add module docstring to `docker_service.py` | pydoc shows overview | 0.25h |\n223: | 4.14.2 | Add class docstring to `DockerService` | Description and usage in docstring | 0.25h |\n224: | 4.14.3 | Add docstrings to all public methods | Args, returns, raises documented | 0.5h |\n225: | 4.14.4 | Add type hints to all method signatures | mypy passes without errors | 0.5h |\n226: \n227: **Deliverable:** Code is well-documented for maintainers.\n228: \n229: ---\n230: \n231: ## ST-4.15 — Lint & Type Check\n232: \n233: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n234: |---|------|--------------|------|\n235: | 4.15.1 | Run `ruff check agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | No lint errors | 0.25h |\n236: | 4.15.2 | Run `mypy agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | No type errors | 0.25h |\n237: | 4.15.3 | Fix any ruff issues | All checks pass | 0.5h |\n238: | 4.15.4 | Fix any mypy issues | All checks pass | 0.5h |\n239: \n240: **Deliverable:** Code passes all lint and type checks.\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ## Summary\n245: \n246: | Phase | Tasks | Est. Hours |\n247: |-------|-------|------------|\n248: | ST-4.1: Core Service Verification | 6 | 1.75h |\n249: | ST-4.2: Image Building Verification | 8 | 2.75h |\n250: | ST-4.3: Image Tagging Verification | 4 | 1.0h |\n251: | ST-4.4: Image Info & Listing Verification | 8 | 2.0h |\n252: | ST-4.5: Image Push Verification | 8 | 2.25h |\n253: | ST-4.6: Credential Extraction Verification | 5 | 1.5h |\n254: | ST-4.7: Service Export Verification | 2 | 0.5h |\n255: | ST-4.8: Unit Tests — Core | 7 | 3.5h |\n256: | ST-4.9: Unit Tests — Build | 9 | 4.5h |\n257: | ST-4.10: Unit Tests — Tag/Info | 8 | 4.0h |\n258: | ST-4.11: Unit Tests — Push | 7 | 3.5h |\n259: | ST-4.12: Unit Tests — Credentials | 5 | 2.5h |\n260: | ST-4.13: Integration Tests | 7 | 5.0h |\n261: | ST-4.14: Documentation | 4 | 1.5h |\n262: | ST-4.15: Lint & Type Check | 4 | 1.5h |\n263: | **Total** | **92** | **37.0h** |\n264: \n265: ---\n266: \n267: ## File Deliverables Checklist\n268: \n269: - [x] `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` — DockerService implementation\n270: - [x] `agentcube/services/__init__.py` — Service exports (DockerService)\n271: - [ ] `tests/unit/test_docker_service_core.py` — Core service unit tests\n272: - [ ] `tests/unit/test_docker_service_build.py` — Image building tests\n273: - [ ] `tests/unit/test_docker_service_tag.py` — Image tagging tests\n274: - [ ] `tests/unit/test_docker_service_info.py` — Image info/listing tests\n275: - [ ] `tests/unit/test_docker_service_push.py` — Image push tests\n276: - [ ] `tests/unit/test_docker_service_credentials.py` — Credential extraction tests\n277: - [ ] `tests/integration/test_docker_service.py` — Integration tests\n278: \n279: ---\n280: \n281: ## Verification Commands\n282: \n283: ```bash\n284: # Install verification\n285: pip install -e \".[dev,test]\"\n286: \n287: # Import verification\n288: python -c \"from agentcube.services import DockerService\"\n289: python -c \"from agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService\"\n290: \n291: # Docker availability check\n292: python -c \"from agentcube.services import DockerService; svc = DockerService(); print(svc.is_docker_available())\"\n293: \n294: # Unit test verification\n295: pytest tests/unit/test_docker_service_core.py -v\n296: pytest tests/unit/test_docker_service_build.py -v\n297: pytest tests/unit/test_docker_service_tag.py -v\n298: pytest tests/unit/test_docker_service_info.py -v\n299: pytest tests/unit/test_docker_service_push.py -v\n300: pytest tests/unit/test_docker_service_credentials.py -v\n301: \n302: # Integration tests (requires Docker)\n303: pytest tests/integration/test_docker_service.py -v\n304: \n305: # Coverage report\n306: pytest --cov=agentcube.services.docker_service --cov-report=term-missing\n307: \n308: # Lint verification\n309: ruff check agentcube/services/docker_service.py\n310: mypy agentcube/services/docker_service.py\n311: ```\n312: \n313: ---\n314: \n315: ## Definition of Done\n316: \n317: - [ ] All 92 tasks complete\n318: - [ ] Package installs successfully (`pip install -e .`)\n319: - [ ] DockerService importable from `agentcube.services`\n320: - [ ] All unit tests pass (>80% coverage for DockerService)\n321: - [ ] Integration tests pass (requires Docker daemon)\n322: - [ ] Type checking passes (`mypy`)\n323: - [ ] Linting passes (`ruff`)\n324: - [ ] Documentation complete with docstrings\n325: \n326: ---\n327: \n328: ## Dependencies\n329: \n330: - `docker>=6.0.0` — Docker SDK for Python (already in pyproject.toml)\n331: - `pytest>=7.4.0` — Testing framework (already present)\n332: - `pytest-cov>=4.1.0` — Coverage reporting (already present)\n333: - `pytest-mock>=3.11.0` — Mocking utilities (already present)\n334: \n335: ---\n336: \n337: ## Design Notes\n338: \n339: - **Backend Strategy:** Primary Docker SDK with error handling; no CLI fallback required per proposal\n340: - **Connection Management:** Lazy initialization with health check via `_get_client()`\n341: - **Error Handling:** RuntimeError for Docker errors, FileNotFoundError for missing files\n342: - **Logging:** Structured logging with self.logger, verbose mode enables DEBUG level\n343: - **Result Formatting:** Image IDs truncated to 12 chars, sizes formatted as \"XX.XXMB\"\n344: - **Credential Extraction:** URL format `user:pass@registry.com/image:tag` with URL decoding\n345: - **Build Args:** Supports proxy configuration via HTTP_PROXY/HTTPS_PROXY build args\n346: \n347: ---\n348: \n349: *AR-024 — Module: cmd/cli — Language: Python — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 349 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n\n> **AR ID:** AR-024  \n> **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n> **Language:** Python  \n> **Size:** M  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `DockerService` class provides a unified, high-level interface for Docker image operations within the AgentCube CLI. This service abstracts Docker SDK interactions for image building, tagging, pushing, and management, providing consistent error handling, logging, and result formatting across the CLI toolchain.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — Core Service Implementation Verification\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775896204705,"end":1775896204726}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896204730,"sessionID":"ses_28456ee41ffeBVl5njyNx1JzXZ","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba97e840010QAdBFp1SjLPQt","messageID":"msg_d7ba96af1001ej62mXlCS3S5GU","sessionID":"ses_28456ee41ffeBVl5njyNx1JzXZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/tests.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/tests.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024: DockerService 封装 — Test Specification\n2: \n3: ## Unit Tests\n4: \n5: ### Service Initialization Tests\n6: - `test_initializes_with_sdk_backend`: Uses docker-py when available\n7: - `test_falls_back_to_cli_backend`: Falls back to CLI when SDK unavailable\n8: - `test_raises_on_no_backend`: Error when neither backend available\n9: - `test_loads_config_from_env`: Config from environment variables\n10: \n11: ### Container Operation Tests\n12: - `test_create_container_calls_sdk`: SDK backend create path\n13: - `test_create_container_calls_cli`: CLI backend create path\n14: - `test_start_container_success`: Container start happy path\n15: - `test_stop_container_with_timeout`: Stop with custom timeout\n16: - `test_remove_container_force`: Force removal\n17: - `test_list_containers_returns_structure`: Proper data structure\n18: - `test_inspect_container_parses_json`: JSON parsing for CLI backend\n19: \n20: ### Image Operation Tests\n21: - `test_pull_image_with_callback`: Progress callback invoked\n22: - `test_pull_image_raises_on_failure`: Error handling\n23: - `test_build_image_with_args`: Build args passed correctly\n24: - `test_list_images_returns_list`: Returns image list\n25: - `test_remove_image_force`: Force image removal\n26: \n27: ### Error Handling Tests\n28: - `test_connection_error_raised`: Connection failures\n29: - `test_not_found_error_raised`: 404 scenarios\n30: - `test_timeout_error_raised`: Operation timeouts\n31: - `test_retry_on_transient_error`: Retry logic\n32: \n33: ## Integration Tests\n34: \n35: ### Happy Path\n36: - `test_full_container_lifecycle`: Create → Start → Stop → Remove\n37: - `test_pull_and_run`: Pull image and run container\n38: - `test_build_and_run`: Build image and run container\n39: \n40: ### Error Scenarios\n41: - `test_invalid_image_name`: Invalid image handling\n42: - `test_port_conflict`: Port already in use\n43: - `test_volume_not_found`: Missing volume\n44: \n45: ## Test Data\n46: - Mock Docker SDK client\n47: - Mock subprocess for CLI backend\n48: - Sample Dockerfile for build tests\n49: - Test container fixtures\n\n(End of file - total 49 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024: DockerService 封装 — Test Specification\n\n## Unit Tests\n\n### Service Initialization Tests\n- `test_initializes_with_sdk_backend`: Uses docker-py when available\n- `test_falls_back_to_cli_backend`: Falls back to CLI when SDK unavailable\n- `test_raises_on_no_backend`: Error when neither backend available\n- `test_loads_config_from_env`: Config from environment variables\n\n### Container Operation Tests\n- `test_create_container_calls_sdk`: SDK backend create path\n- `test_create_container_calls_cli`: CLI backend create path\n- `test_start_container_success`: Container start happy path\n- `test_stop_container_with_timeout`: Stop with custom timeout\n- `test_remove_container_force`: Force removal\n- `test_list_containers_returns_structure`: Proper data structure\n- `test_inspect_container_parses_json`: JSON parsing for CLI backend\n\n### Image Operation Tests","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/tests.md","time":{"start":1775896204709,"end":1775896204729}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896204732,"sessionID":"ses_28456ee41ffeBVl5njyNx1JzXZ","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba987b2001gFwWBq45hHy42X","messageID":"msg_d7ba96af1001ej62mXlCS3S5GU","sessionID":"ses_28456ee41ffeBVl5njyNx1JzXZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/notes.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/notes.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024: DockerService 封装 — Notes\n2: \n3: ## Status\n4: Initialized: 2026-04-11\n5: \n6: ## Open Questions\n7: - Should we enforce minimum Docker API version?\n8: - How to handle Docker Compose scenarios?\n9: - Should we support podman as alternative backend?\n10: - What logging level is appropriate for Docker operations?\n11: \n12: ## References\n13: - See AR-023 for K8sProvider implementation patterns\n14: - Related to container deployment architecture\n15: - Check existing docker_service.py for any reusable code\n16: \n17: ## Change Log\n18: - 2026-04-11: Initial scaffold created\n\n(End of file - total 18 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024: DockerService 封装 — Notes\n\n## Status\nInitialized: 2026-04-11\n\n## Open Questions\n- Should we enforce minimum Docker API version?\n- How to handle Docker Compose scenarios?\n- Should we support podman as alternative backend?\n- What logging level is appropriate for Docker operations?\n\n## References\n- See AR-023 for K8sProvider implementation patterns\n- Related to container deployment architecture\n- Check existing docker_service.py for any reusable code\n\n## Change Log\n- 2026-04-11: Initial scaffold created","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/notes.md","time":{"start":1775896204712,"end":1775896204731}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896204735,"sessionID":"ses_28456ee41ffeBVl5njyNx1JzXZ","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba98f11001yVeMB4fU2bgwZc","messageID":"msg_d7ba96af1001ej62mXlCS3S5GU","sessionID":"ses_28456ee41ffeBVl5njyNx1JzXZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024: DockerService 封装 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: This document describes the delta specification for implementing the DockerService\n5: encapsulation layer in the cmd/cli module.\n6: \n7: ## Current State\n8: - Docker operations scattered in various places\n9: - No unified abstraction for container management\n10: - Direct subprocess calls to docker CLI in some places\n11: - Limited error handling for Docker operations\n12: \n13: ## Target State\n14: A unified DockerService class that:\n15: - Provides clean abstraction over Docker operations\n16: - Supports both Docker SDK and CLI fallback\n17: - Offers comprehensive error handling\n18: - Returns structured data\n19: - Supports async operations\n20: \n21: ## Delta Analysis\n22: \n23: ### New Components\n24: 1. **DockerService** (`cmd/cli/internal/docker_service.py`)\n25:    - Main service class with all Docker operations\n26:    - Backend selection (SDK/CLI)\n27:    - Connection management\n28: \n29: 2. **Docker Exceptions** (`cmd/cli/internal/docker_exceptions.py`)\n30:    - DockerError base class\n31:    - ConnectionError, ImageNotFoundError, etc.\n32: \n33: 3. **Configuration** (`cmd/cli/internal/docker_config.py`)\n34:    - DockerConnectionConfig dataclass\n35:    - Environment variable parsing\n36: \n37: ### Modified Components\n38: - None (this is a new service layer)\n39: \n40: ### Dependencies\n41: - docker-py library (optional, for SDK backend)\n42: - Existing subprocess utilities for CLI backend\n43: \n44: ## Interface Specification\n45: \n46: ### DockerService Class\n47: ```python\n48: class DockerService:\n49:     def __init__(self, config: DockerConfig = None)\n50:     def create_container(self, image: str, **kwargs) -> Container\n51:     def start_container(self, container_id: str) -> None\n52:     def stop_container(self, container_id: str, timeout: int = 30) -> None\n53:     def remove_container(self, container_id: str, force: bool = False) -> None\n54:     def list_containers(self, all: bool = False) -> List[Container]\n55:     def pull_image(self, image: str, callback: Callable = None) -> Image\n56:     def build_image(self, path: str, tag: str, **kwargs) -> Image\n57:     def list_images(self) -> List[Image]\n58:     def remove_image(self, image_id: str, force: bool = False) -> None\n59: ```\n60: \n61: ## Implementation Notes\n62: - Prefer Docker SDK when available\n63: - Fallback to CLI for operations not supported by SDK\n64: - All methods should accept timeout parameter\n65: - Progress callbacks for long operations\n\n(End of file - total 65 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024: DockerService 封装 — Delta Spec\n\n## Overview\nThis document describes the delta specification for implementing the DockerService\nencapsulation layer in the cmd/cli module.\n\n## Current State\n- Docker operations scattered in various places\n- No unified abstraction for container management\n- Direct subprocess calls to docker CLI in some places\n- Limited error handling for Docker operations\n\n## Target State\nA unified DockerService class that:\n- Provides clean abstraction over Docker operations\n- Supports both Docker SDK and CLI fallback\n- Offers comprehensive error handling\n- Returns structured data\n- Supports async operations\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775896204714,"end":1775896204732}}}}
